Why this file exists, and what it is not
----------------------------------------

An absent LICENSE file is ambiguous: a reader cannot tell whether the author
forgot, or intended to reserve all rights. This file removes the ambiguity.
Under default copyright, the effect is the same either way -- all rights are
reserved -- but saying so plainly is the honest thing to do, and this project
holds itself to the rule that its stated posture must match its real one.

A permissive or source-available licence may be granted in the future. If and
when that happens, it will appear here.

This notice is a statement of intent by the copyright holder. It is not legal
advice, and it has not been reviewed by a lawyer.

Dependencies retain their own licences. jobtree depends on Kubernetes,
controller-runtime, and other components that are separately licensed
(predominantly Apache-2.0); nothing here alters those terms.
